HEADWORD: Mastigophora
<hw>Mas"ti*go*phor`a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>ma`stix</grk>, <grk>ma`stigos</grk>, a whip +
<grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A phylum of
protozoans the kingdom <kingdom>Protista</kingdom>, consisting mainly of
free-living flagellated unicellular organisms, lacking photosynthetic
capability. Some members are pathogenic in man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

